    <string name="help">Help</string>
    <string name="help_overview_heading">Overview</string>
    <string name="help_settings_heading">Settings</string>
    <string name="help_customize">Customizing Settings</string>
    <string name="help_customize_summary">In the settings section of the menu you can set default behaviour for the
        statistics and notifications.
        Initially both are turned off. By switching the corresponding button you can choose to turn statistics and
        notifications on / off per default.
    </string>
    <string name="help_category_general_features">General Features</string>
    <string name="help_category_reminder">Reminder</string>
    <string name="help_category_statistics">Statistics</string>
    <string name="help_privacy_heading">Privacy Info</string>
    <string name="help_permissionXY_heading">Permission for camera access</string>
    <string name="help_permissionXY_description">This permission is needed in order to be able to take a picture and add
        it
        to a product. If this permission is denied, this feature cannot be used. Denying this permission will not
        affect any of the other features.
    </string>
    <string name="help_permissions_heading">Permissions</string>
    <string name="help_permissions_description">Other permissions are not required.</string>
    <string name="help_intro_long_general">
        You can create, delete, remove and sort lists. Inside a list you are able to add, edit, remove and sort items
        as well. The items in a list can be marked as \"bought\" by using a checkbox. As soon as an item is checked, it
        goes to the end of the list. If the statistics are enabled for the current list, then the relevant information
        will be save in the statistics every time an item is checked.
    </string>
    <string name="help_intro_reminder">
        Reminders are showed through notifications. In order to see them, you need to enable the notifications in the
        settings section.
    </string>
    <string name="help_intro_statistics">
        The statistics section shows a summary of the purchased items. The diagram can be filtered by a date range. You
        can select whether you want to group the results by month, week, day, category, store or product name.
        Additionally,
        you can select whether total amount (price) or quantity (units) should be shown.
    </string>
    <string name="help_intro">Welcome to the help page of Privacy Friendly Shopping List. This app allows you to manage
        your shopping lists. Besides giving each list a name you can set a priority, deadline, reminder
        and add notes to each of them. Additionally, you can decide whether a list should keep track of its checked
        items in order summarize them in the statistics section.\n\n
        A shopping list contains products. You can setup quantity, price, store, and category for each of them.
        Furthermore,
        you can write notes and use the camera to add an image.
    </string>

